Subject: Australian Journal of Linguistics 
To: Ronald
Content:
The Australian Journal of Linguistics is a quarterly peer-reviewed academic journal in the field of linguistics established in 1981. It is the official journal of the Australian Linguistic Society and is published by Routledge. Its main focus is theoretical linguistics, as well as matters pertaining particularly to Australia such as Australian English and its indigenous languages. The current editor-in-chief is Keith Allan.
